Apple Pie
via Joy of Cooking https://www.keyingredient.com/recipes/114377392/joy-of-cooking-apple-pie/

5 to 6 cups apples, peeled, cored and sliced
1/2 to 2/3 cup white sugar (modify sugar amount based on tartness of apples)
1/8 teaspoon salt
1 to 1 1/2 tablespoon cornstarch (modify cornstarch based on juiciness of apples)
1/4 teaspoon cinnamon
1/8 teaspoon nutmeg
1 1/2 tablespoon unsalted butter

If apples are bland sprinkle with:
1 tablespoon lemon juice
1 teaspoon vanilla

Preheat oven to 450°F. Prepare unbaked pie crust in 9-inch pie pan. 

Stir apples and all ingredients except butter gently until coated.  If mixture is dry, add some water or lemon juice.

Place in layers in pie shell. Dot with butter.

Cover pie with pricked upper crust.

Bake 10 minutes at 450°F. Reduce heat to 350°F and bake until done, 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. 

Brush top with milk and sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
